<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-05-28T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-05-28T14:00:00-05:00" n="1473" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1473">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">125.8571/5–2649: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Cabot</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-05-28T15:00:00-04:00">May 28,
                                    1949—3 p. m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1081. Asst. Secy Rusk discussed substance urtel 1840 May 26 with Amb Koo
                            same day quoting ur statement that “Nationalists have wantonly fired on
                            Amer flag”. Rusk told Koo Dept did not intend give publicity this matter
                            but indicated Dept’s deep concern over report. Koo stated wld immed wire
                            Chi Govt, Canton, urging cessation firing by Nationalists on US Govt
                            property.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Webb</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>